

Returns the full block information along with its receipts.

## Parameters

- `ctx` - The context of the request.
- `blockID` - The block identifier. Can be:
  - Block hash
  - Block number
  - "latest" for the latest block
  - "pending" for the pending block

## Returns

Returns a block object containing:
- Block header information
- Transaction receipts
- Other block-related data

## Example

```go
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"
	"log"
	"github.com/NethermindEth/starknet.go/rpc"

	"encoding/json"
)

func main() {
	rpcUrl := "https://free-rpc.nethermind.io/mainnet-juno/"
	provider, err := rpc.NewProvider(rpcUrl)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	result, err := provider.BlockWithReceipts(context.Background(), rpc.BlockID{Tag: "latest"})
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}
	formartedResult, err := json.MarshalIndent(result, "", "  ")
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}
	fmt.Println("Block with receipts: ", string(formartedResult))
}
```
